House Bill 840 (AS PASSED HOUSE AND SENATE)
By: Representative Jasperse of the 11th
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To repeal an Act creating the Pickens County Airport Authority, approved April 19, 2006
2 (Ga. L. 2006, p. 3645), as amended; to provide for the assets and liabilities thereof; to repeal
3 conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
5 SECTION 1.
6 An Act creating the Pickens County Airport Authority, approved April 19, 2006 (Ga. L.
7 2006, p. 3645), as amended, is hereby repealed in its entirety.
8 SECTION 2.
9 Any and all assets of the Pickens County Airport Authority shall devolve automatically and
10 without further action to Pickens County, Georgia. The Board of Commissioners of Pickens
11 County, Georgia, is authorized to execute any deeds or instruments of conveyance required
12 to place title of such assets into the name of Pickens County and is authorized to do so in the
13 name of the Pickens County Airport Authority. The obligations of the Pickens County
14 Airport Authority shall be transferred to and assumed by Pickens County, Georgia, by such
15 instruments as may be required to maintain the same. The Board of Commissioners of
